  "html": "<h1>Applies to</h1>\n  <ul>\n    <li>PCI DSS Requirement 3.6.7</li>\n  </ul>\n  <h1>What to Check For</h1>\n  <p>Key management procedures should be implemented to prevent unauthorized key substitution.</p>\n  <h1>Why</h1>\n  <p>Unauthorized key substitution means that an attacker can substitute one of the authorized keys and gain access to sensitive information without raising alarm.\n</p>\n  <h1>How to Check</h1>\n  <p>Check the key management procedures in the information security policy to make sure there are provisions for preventing unauthorized key substitution.</p>\n  <h1>How to Fix</h1>\n  <p>Make a table of authorized keys (known as a keystore) and use only those keys for encryption.&amp;nbsp;Whenever changes are made to the table of keys, make sure the changes are authorized.&amp;nbsp;Document the implementation of the key table and the update mechanism in the\n key management procedures in the information security policy.</p>\n  <h1>Additional Resources</h1>\n  <ul>\n    <li>For more information about key management procedures, please see <a href=\"http://csrc.nist.gov/\">\nhttp://csrc.nist.gov</a> &amp;nbsp; </li>\n    <li>For more information about designing and documenting key management procedures, please see&amp;nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.net-security.org/article.php?id=1185\">http://www.net-security.org/article.php?id=1185</a></li>\n  </ul>\n  <h1>Related Items</h1>\n  <ul>\n    <li>\n      <p>\n        <a href=\"/article/9bb67e82-ea00-4a56-95fd-67720041afe6\">Prepare the Key Management Procedures</a>\n      </p>\n    </li>\n  </ul>"
